spanGrp.span: Oh, there was a mister chased by a horse.
A pekaga kajali töjiá kabayö të
He locked himself in in a place with a wild cat.
(_) Jekepa jẽk kötiá-wã mãĩ kãrbö blali ska
He got so scared that he walked very quietly.
Ñerö jeska í mẽletenã'-wã tã'ĩ shkö-gẽ bitaba bitaba
He saw that he could go through and tried to open the door and there the wild cat roared at him;
(_) mãga í sũã'-ite „jiwa s-kömĩsãũ“ ñerö í wöyawã (m) í köyá-ite Ñerö jeska bö nẽ nãmã anã' í wö jãrga
so, he let the door loose and he thought he would walk very quietly.
í já-ite plaja begetsá-ite shkö-mĩ ĩã bitaba bitaba
He then crashed his elbow against the wild car´s water;
Ñerö í julañãk kenã' mãĩ kãrbö diglö blali ska
he hit him, grabbed him and let him quietly.
Ñerö je kenã'ũ-mĩ gugá-ñẽ-ite kamã'-ite bitaba
He thought he could take a piece of clothing and shake it so someone could see him.
Í begetsá-ite mãga estee sua taglö yasã'-ite jue-gẽ-ite pe-wa í sũã-glö yurö të yurölë wã í sũã-glö
only a dog came by which bit him steadily
Ta chichi bö beteũ í kue-gate í kue-gate
and there is where the lady saw him.
He thought about kicking the dog with the foot, but the dog bit it, his foot.
begetsá-ite chichi tiá-ite klö wa ñẽ je chichi të í gugá kwá-ite í klöga
The lady approached, he kicked (the dog)on the head (laughing).
Ñẽ pemina jẽk sigá-wã í gugá-wã tiá í tsagu bataga (laughs)
The dog... the lady lost her air and falled down.
Then... oh, he was sprinkling her with water;
Ñerö a jie të diglö jũe-gate pemina siwã' janã-mĩ ĩã
so, the wild cat woke up and the man tried to hide himself behind the bars;
ñẽ kãrbö shkinã-ka í wagi jẽk jẽk yotowã' kal mẽ bitaba
the cat came by to smell him and did not do anything to him and went back to sleep.
kãrbö beteũte jalaksá Ka mẽnẽwã-nẽ ĩã mẽnẽũ jẽk baglachá
The man was really glad the wild cat did no harm to him.
Ñerö í wagi jẽk sánã „ka wã s-mẽwanẽ ĩã“
The lady stood up and spoke to him; she opened the door for him and said
Pemina shkina-gate she-gẽ ĩã (_) jũkö yasá ĩã
“¡come! It does not do me anything. It does not do me anything. Wait for me!”
„¡Ba shkö-te í rö“ Jebi shá-ite pemina ĩã „¡sũã'-ugö ka í të s-mẽwẽ ¡sũã-'ugö Ka í të s-mẽwẽ ¡S-kĩksöpa“
He thought about coming closer to the wild cat and so he did.
Begetsá-ite mĩ jamĩkegla í jẽk sigá-wã jamĩkegla
But the wild cat roared at him and he passed quickly by.
Ñẽ kãrbö anã' í wö jãrga Í káũ plaja
and the asshole went up on a tree and waived to the lady;
je chi mẽnẽga kaljula nã Jula kashö-gẽ pemina ĩã
she told him to come down,
Pemina të she-gẽ „¡ba jẽk jawãsã' ba jẽk jawãsã'“
but would no listen to her.
Then the lady was there and so he jumped down suddenly and there it ended.’
Ñerö pemina kel jeska nẽbónẽ jeska je bá plaja Ñerö jeska onã'-wã
